Only about 30 percent of all bank branches are in rural areas where over 60 per cent of India’s population lives. This one data point shows the major gap in access to formal sources of credit and dependence on informal money lenders in the country’s rural markets and even in tier 2 and 3 markets. Piramal Finance is attempting to bridge this divide through its products, media strategies and marketing initiatives that break conventional perceptions about credit access. 

In a conversation with @delshadirani9 , Jairam Sridharan, managing director of Piramal Finance and the company’s chief marketing officer Arvind Iyer, share what makes the “Budget Customers of Bharat” tick and how Piramal Finance is addressing the needs of the under-served people of Bharat market.

Watch Media Dialogues with @brandstoryboard on CNBC-TV18 on Wednesday, Saturday and Sunday.

#businessnews #businessnewstoday #businessnewsinenglish #cnbctv18 #Storyboard18 #Mediadialogues #PiramalFinance #Housing #Finance
